word: gates of the arctic national park and preserve

uk: ˌɡeɪts əv ði ˌɑːk.tɪk ˌnæʃ.ən.əl ˌpɑːk ən prɪˈzɜːv
us: ˌɡeɪts əv ði ˌɑːrk.tɪk ˌnæʃ.ən.əl ˌpɑːrk ən prɪˈzɜ˞ːv

body_content.explanation: a national park (= a large area of land protected by the government because of its natural beauty or because it has a special history) in the US state of Alaska:
examples: There are no roads in Gates of the Arctic National Park and Preserve.
Experienced hikers consider six miles a good day’s travel in Gates of the Arctic National Park and Preserve.
